This report was completed using information from Wendell Mathews, Tri-County Natural Gas Authority. Tri-County merged with City of Greensboro and Union Point. A 100% system-wide survey was completed in 2022 for the newly formed Authority. Based on the results of this survey, this report reflects the total mileage of main and number of services system-wide. There was a discrepancy of 157 services and 3.29 miles of main between the system-wide survey and the 2021 7100 reports from the three separate systems, which has been adjusted in this report. Also, due to the lack of records, the mains and services reported by decade of installation have now been adjusted to show all pipe previously reported as pre-1990 in the "unknown" decade. The LAUF has also been re-calculated to ensure that the 3 separate systems' data was combined correctly prior to the merger, which occurred during the year. There were evidently some inaccuracies in the LAUF calculation with the mid-year merger, but the current year (7/2022 - 6/2023) LAUF is tracking within the +/- 2% tolerance.

OPERATOR_NAME: EPCOR GAS TEXAS DEVELOPMENT AND SERVICES INC.

ADDITIONAL_INFORMATION: Pipeline is in Idol state with no pressure on the line. Planned abandonment in progress. The Pipeline originates at the South Pass 60A OCS federal platform as 10" Segment #3655. The pipeline continues into LA state waters in the SP 6 block where it previously boarded a metering deck that has been removed. The 10" line ties into a 6" line then crosses numerous passes (several navigable waterways) before entering Targa's Venice Gas Plant in Plaquemines Parish. Within the plant, available gas is sent to the Delta Gathering System or processed gas may be returned to the SP 60 facility through buy-back metering from the plant residue gas. Pipeline path is through uninhabited marshland except for segment between SP 60A and SP 6 Federal/State line.
